
==Definition==

Sordini is the italian word for mute, commonly used in music.  
It is used as in ''con sordini'', which means "with mute"  ''Senza sordini'' means without mute.  Also used is ''sordini altazi'' and ''sordini levati'', which both mean, lift mute.  Comes from the words ''sorda'', ''sordo'', and ''sordamente'', all of which mean "Dull in tone, muffled"
Other names are sordina, and sordino.  

